
[1]bigot

   BIG'OT, n.

   1. A person who is obstinately and unreasonably wedded to a particular
   religious creed, opinion, practice or ritual. The word is sometimes
   used in an enlarged sense, for a person who is illiberally attached to
   any opinion, or system of belief; as a bigot to the Mohammedan
   religion; a bigot to a form of government.

   2. A venetian liquid measure containing the fourth part of the amphor,
   or half the boot.

                                   BIG'OT
